@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #F8F9FA

title AI Crop Advisory System - Recommendation Sequence

actor "Farmer" as farmer
participant "React UI\n(Form)" as UI
participant "API Client" as API
participant "Flask API" as Flask
participant "Pydantic\nValidator" as Valid
participant "Weather\nService" as Weather
participant "OpenWeatherMap" as OWM
participant "Gemini AI\nService" as Gemini
participant "Google Gemini" as GeminiAPI
participant "Logger" as Log

== Form Submission ==
farmer -> UI: Fill multi-step form
activate UI
UI -> UI: Validate input locally
UI -> API: Submit form data
activate API
API -> API: Show loading animation
API -> Flask: POST /api/recommend\n{location, season, budget,\nland_size, soil_type, irrigation}
activate Flask

== Request Validation ==
Flask -> Log: Log incoming request
Flask -> Valid: Validate request body
activate Valid
Valid -> Valid: Check required fields
Valid -> Valid: Validate data types
Valid --> Flask: Validated data
deactivate Valid

== Weather Data Fetch ==
Flask -> Weather: get_weather(lat, lon)
activate Weather
Weather -> OWM: GET current weather
activate OWM
OWM --> Weather: {temp, humidity, wind, rain}
deactivate OWM
Weather -> OWM: GET 5-day forecast
activate OWM
OWM --> Weather: {forecast_data}
deactivate OWM
Weather -> Weather: Process & summarize
Weather --> Flask: weather_summary
deactivate Weather

== AI Recommendation ==
Flask -> Gemini: get_recommendations(\nweather, location, season,\nbudget, land, soil, irrigation)
activate Gemini
Gemini -> Gemini: Build structured prompt
Gemini -> GeminiAPI: Generate content
activate GeminiAPI
note right
  AI analyzes:
  - Weather conditions
  - Soil compatibility
  - Budget constraints
  - Irrigation availability
  - Seasonal suitability
  - Market trends
end note
GeminiAPI --> Gemini: AI response (JSON)
deactivate GeminiAPI
Gemini -> Gemini: Parse JSON response
Gemini -> Gemini: Validate crop structure
Gemini -> Gemini: Add UI hints (colors, gradients)
Gemini --> Flask: 3 crop recommendations
deactivate Gemini

== Response Building ==
Flask -> Flask: Build response JSON:\n- weather\n- recommendations (3 crops)\n- market_insights\n- timestamp
Flask -> Log: Log successful response

Flask --> API: 200 OK\n{weather, recommendations, market_insights}
deactivate Flask

== UI Update ==
API -> API: Hide loading animation
API -> UI: Update state with data
deactivate API
UI -> UI: Render weather summary
UI -> UI: Render crop cards with animations
UI -> UI: Render market insights
UI --> farmer: Display recommendations
deactivate UI

== User Interaction ==
farmer -> UI: Expand crop card
activate UI
UI -> UI: Animate expansion
UI -> UI: Show cultivation steps
UI -> UI: Show risk assessment
UI --> farmer: Detailed information
deactivate UI

@enduml
